Allmon README

- Install instructions
 - Put these files somwhere in your web servers document tree. That can be the docroot or any subdir you like. 

 - Copy and edit the INI file
 Copy allmon.ini.txt to allmon.ini and then edit it for your node(s) information.
 The user ID and passwords are the one you will use in manager.conf on your server(s).

 - Create your .htpasswd file.
 This creates your admin login ID and password. In your web server directory, on the command line do:
 htpasswd -c .htpasswd username

 - Make sure you have the latest Allstar source from svn

 - Edit /etc/asterisk/monitor.conf
